TWENTY-FOURTH NORTHERN MARIANAS COMMONWEALTH
LEGISLATURE
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
Regular Session, 2025 H. B. 24- 76
A BILL FOR AN ACT
To authorize the Public School System (PSS) to utilize
unrestricted funds previously appropriated to PSS for Fiscal
Year 2026; and for other purposes.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE 24TH NORTHERN MARIANAS
COMMONWEALTH LEGISLATURE:
1 Section 1. Findings and Purpose. The Legislature finds that the Public
2 School System (PSS) requested through the budget process for Fiscal Year 2026
3 the amount of $49,285,559.00. The Legislature further finds that Public Law 24-
4 14 (the Fiscal Year 2026 Budget) only allocated $31,779,008.00 for PSS, which is
5 a difference of $17,506,551.00. Additionally, the Legislature finds that PSS has
6 unrestricted funds available for its usage in the amount of $4,911,849.00 but needs
7 legislative action in order to utilize the funds.
8 Therefore, the intent of this Act is to allow PSS to utilize $4,911,849.00 of
9 its unrestricted funds for Fiscal Year 2026.
10 Section 2. Enactment. Notwithstanding any laws, rules or regulations to
11 the contrary PSS is hereby authorized to utilize $4,911,849.00 of its unrestricted
12 funds for Fiscal Year 2026.

